Class ValueCollectionPopulatedTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.ValueCollectionPopulatedTests
public class ValueCollectionPopulatedTests extends Object
Test case for ValueCollection when the underlying map is populated. This class tests the behavior of ValueCollection methods when there are elements in the map.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
  • MapAdapter.ValueCollection
Design
This test is designed to ensure that the ValueCollection behaves correctly when the underlying map is populated, specifically checking size(), isEmpty(), contains(), iterator(), toArray(), add(), remove(), containsAll(), addAll(), retainAll(), removeAll(), clear(), equals(), and hashCode() methods.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3
